gitCommit.subject: Remove sidebar footer and move Privacy/Terms links to the settings sidebar; clean up related styles and navigation logic.
gitCommit.body:
Remove sidebar footer and move Privacy/Terms links to the settings sidebar; clean up related styles and navigation logic.

- Dropped the `navigateTo` helper and the footer markup from `Sidebar.tsx`, eliminating the in‑sidebar privacy/terms links.
- Deleted the corresponding CSS rules (`.sidebarFooter`, `.footerSeparator`) from `Sidebar.module.css`.
- Added Privacy and Terms entries to the settings navigation list in `SettingsSidebar.tsx`, preserving access to these pages via the settings UI.

gitCommit.subject: Remove sidebar footer and move Privacy/Terms links to the settings sidebar; clean up related styles and navigation logic.
gitCommit.body:
Remove sidebar footer and move Privacy/Terms links to the settings sidebar; clean up related styles and navigation logic.

- Dropped the `navigateTo` helper and the footer markup from `Sidebar.tsx`, eliminating the in‑sidebar privacy/terms links.
- Deleted the corresponding CSS rules (`.sidebarFooter`, `.footerSeparator`) from `Sidebar.module.css`.
- Added Privacy and Terms entries to the settings navigation list in `SettingsSidebar.tsx`, preserving access to these pages via the settings UI.
